				 Coke plans expansion
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, Dec.3: Coca-Cola will invest $250 million over the next three years to expand its operations in India. 																								Muhtar Kent, president and chief operating officer of The Coca-Cola Company, said, This money will be used to increase bottling capacities and devise innovative distribution models. Kent was speaking on the sidelines of the India Economic Summit here today. 																								Kent said Coca-Cola is growing in India rapidly, quarter after quarter. We need to invest in infrastructure to ensure that the growth continues.																								Coca-Cola plans to open more bottling plants across the country. The company has 61 bottling units in India. Coca-Cola owns around 65 per cent of these plants, while the others operate on a franchisee basis. 
